  "nbformat": 4,
  "nbformat_minor": 5,
  "metadata": {
    "kernelspec": {
      "name": "maxima",
      "display_name": "Maxima",
      "language": "maxima"
    },
    "aximar": {}
  },
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Beam Deflection Analysis\n\nThis notebook analyses beam deflection using the Euler-Bernoulli beam theory. We derive the governing ODE symbolically, obtain the exact closed-form solution for a simply supported beam under uniform load, and then solve the same problem numerically using the finite difference method.\n\nA convergence study validates the numerical approach, and we compute derived quantities (bending moment, shear force) both symbolically and numerically.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "load(\"numerics\")$\nload(\"ax-plots\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 1,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Euler-Bernoulli Beam Equation [S+N]\n\nThe Euler-Bernoulli beam equation governs the deflection $y(x)$ of a slender beam under transverse loading:\n\n$$EI \\frac{d^4 y}{dx^4} = w(x)$$\n\nwhere $EI$ is the flexural rigidity (product of Young's modulus and second moment of area) and $w(x)$ is the distributed load per unit length. For a simply supported beam of length $L$ with uniform load $w_0$, the boundary conditions are:\n\n$$y(0) = 0, \\quad y''(0) = 0, \\quad y(L) = 0, \\quad y''(L) = 0$$",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Beam equation: EI * y''''(x) = w(x) */\n/* Simply supported beam of length L with uniform load w0 */\ndepends(y, x)$\nbeam_eqn : EI * diff(y, x, 4) = w0;\nprint(\"Governing equation:\", beam_eqn)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 2,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "EI*'diff(y,x,4) = w0\nGoverning equation: EI*'diff(y,x,4) = w0"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Symbolic Solution for Simple Cases\n\nFor a uniform load $w(x) = w_0$, the 4th-order ODE can be solved by direct integration four times, introducing four constants of integration $C_1, C_2, C_3, C_4$. Applying the four boundary conditions for a simply supported beam determines all constants uniquely.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* General solution by integrating 4 times */\ny_general : integrate(integrate(integrate(integrate(w0/EI, x), x), x), x)$\n/* Add integration constants */\ny_general : y_general + C1*x^3/6 + C2*x^2/2 + C3*x + C4$\nprint(\"General solution:\", y_general)$\n\n/* Apply BCs: y(0) = 0, y''(0) = 0, y(L) = 0, y''(L) = 0 */\neqs : [subst(x=0, y_general) = 0,\n       subst(x=0, diff(y_general, x, 2)) = 0,\n       subst(x=L, y_general) = 0,\n       subst(x=L, diff(y_general, x, 2)) = 0]$\nprint(\"Boundary conditions:\")$\nfor eq in eqs do print(\"  \", eq)$\n\nsol : solve(eqs, [C1, C2, C3, C4])$\nprint(\"Integration constants:\", sol[1])$\n\ny_exact : subst(sol[1], y_general)$\ny_exact : ratsimp(y_exact);\nprint(\"Exact deflection y(x) =\", y_exact)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 3,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "General solution: (w0*x^4)/(24*EI)+(C1*x^3)/6+(C2*x^2)/2+C3*x+C4\nBoundary conditions:\n   C4 = 0\n   C2 = 0\n   (L^4*w0)/(24*EI)+(C1*L^3)/6+(C2*L^2)/2+C3*L+C4 = 0\n   (L^2*w0)/(2*EI)+C1*L+C2 = 0\nIntegration constants:\n                      [C1 = -((L*w0)/(2*EI)),C2 = 0,C3 = (L^3*w0)/(24*EI),\n                       C4 = 0]\n(w0*x^4-2*L*w0*x^3+L^3*w0*x)/(24*EI)\nExact deflection y(x) = (w0*x^4-2*L*w0*x^3+L^3*w0*x)/(24*EI)"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Substitute numeric values and plot the exact deflection */\nparams : [EI=1, w0=1, L=10]$\ny_plot : subst(params, y_exact)$\n\nax_draw2d(\n  color=\"blue\", line_width=2, name=\"Exact deflection\",\n  explicit(y_plot, x, 0, 10),\n  title=\"Simply Supported Beam \\u2014 Exact Solution\",\n  xlabel=\"Position x\", ylabel=\"Deflection y\",\n  grid=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 4,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
